📈 6. Evaluation Metrics

The paper evaluates image quality using two complementary metrics:

- L2-norm — the mean squared pixel difference between the generated face and the ground-truth photo. Lower = closer at the pixel level.
- SSIM (Structural Similarity Index) — a perceptual metric that compares luminance, contrast, and structure. Higher = more visually similar in terms of facial structure.

The authors also experiment with different weightings of pixel loss vs. contextual loss to find the sweet spot between raw pixel accuracy and holistic image quality. The paper includes:
